title: Print, 1664
inscribed:
Engraved on the plate at lower left:  "Israel Silvestre, deline, et sculpsit parisus"
Inscription on banner at lower center:  "Festin du Roy, et des Reynes, avec plusiers Princesses et Dames, serui de tous lest mets et presens faits par les Dieux et les quatre saisons"
On left side of banner: "Premiere"
Right side: "Journee"
Numbered at lower right:  "6"
creditline: Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt
description: Horizontal rectangle:  In the foreground, a banner, and above a frieze of the back of an audience.  On stage, a procession of servants carrying banquet platters on their heads.  A banquet table with seated guests in the background.

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, 1664.
1664. Black ink on rolled paper. Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt. 1931-86-54.
